While the second phase has officially begun and some senior citizens around the country have received their first jabs, some are feeling confused and anxious. Masego Rahlaga spoke to some senior citizens in Diepsloot, Johannesburg. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Fear and anxiety. That's how some of the elderly say they are feeling as they draw closer to getting their COVID-19 jabs. Government began with Phase 2 of its rollout on Monday READ: Phase 2 rollout: Mkhize allays COVID-19 vaccine fears People aged 60, as well as those with comorbidities, are the target. Some elders in Diepsloot say they wish someone could sit down with them and explain to them properly about the different vaccines and the coronavirus pandemic in general. * eNCA's Masego Rahlaga reports.